main event: A private investigator reported observing a luminous unidentified flying object near Duluth, Minnesota on July 17, 1952.
interesting points: The object emitted a glow resembling a filament light., It was sighted for a few minutes through a telescope., The object suddenly vanished without leaving a trail or sound., There were potentially four similar objects following the lead object., The report describes the object as blunt-nosed and circular shaped.
